article.headline: SE Missouri 81, Morehead St. 78
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Southeast Missouri State built a 15-point lead late in the first half and then held on for an 81-78 win over Morehead State on Thursday. Terrick Willoughby led Missouri State (10-15, 8-8 Ohio Valley) with a season-high 17 points. Brandon Foust scored 14, Roderick Pearson had 13 and Michael Rembert added 10 for the Redhawks. Morehead State (10-13, 6-9), which has lost seven straight games, scored 30 points in the paint in the second half to work its way back into the game. Southeast Missouri hit 9-of-14 3-pointers in the first half and led 45-36 at the break. With the game tied at 75-75 with 2:18 left in the game, Foust hit a 3-pointer to put the Redhawks up for good. Pearson hit two free throws with 13 seconds left for the final margin. The Eagles were led by Quentin Pryor with 16 points, Shaun Williams had 15 and Jamyron Steward added 10.
